$$.value: It's a place where, armed with Cash, you'll be able to purchase accessories, clothes, messenger item, hair salon coupons, coupons for plastic surgery, and other various items.
The window that allows the character to see the items it owns.\nThe items are categorized under Equip., Use, Set-Up, and Etc. items.
The window that shows the equipped items, and allowing the character to equip/unequip them.\nOpen the item inventory alongside it to use the equip. items.
The window that shows detailed character info and its abilities.\nUse AP to enhance many different kinds of abilities.
The window that shows the detailed look of the skillbook owned by the character.\nUse skill points to learn the skills available.
The window that lets you chat with buddies within a world.
The window that lets you change the options or game infos.\nCan change game and system option.\nCan also see quest info, party info, and the community info.
Press the button to choose the character you want to whisper to.\nPress it once more to disable whisper.
Registers the map the character is at to the teleport list. Can save up to 5 maps.
Registers the map where the character is located into the Teleport List. Can register upto 10 different places.
Delete the chosen map from the list.
Teleports to the map of your choice, or to the map where the chosen character is.
Click on Quest Alarm button if you wish to register the current quest into the Quest Alarm. Up to 5 quests can be registered in this alarm.

Can make the job advancement to Warrior, Bowman, Thief, Magician, or Pirate. 
Warrior : Minimum of Level 10, STR 35. Perion
Bowman : Minimum of Level 10, DEX 25. Henesys
Magician : Minimum of Level 8, INT 20. Ellinia
Thief : Minimum of Level 10, DEX 25. Kerning City
Pirate : Minimum of Level 10, DEX 20. The Nautilus
The main community of the communities the account belongs to.
It's a health stat, and if it reaches 0, the character dies.\nHP decreases if either attacked by an enemy or if a certain skill is used.\nIt can go up to the maximum of 10,000 points.
The stat needed to use various skills.\nIt can go up to the maximum of 10,000 points.
The amount of experience gained. \nObtained by killing a monster or completing a quest.
The stat needed to use heavy weapons and/or armors.\nIt determines the attacking ability of the warriors.
This stat is vital to making direct attacks using a weapon. This is the most significant stat when it comes to the strength of the attacks for warriors and pirates (Brawlers).
The higher this stat, the higher the accuracy of your shooting as well as your avoidability. The most important stat that determines the stregnth of attacks for bowman and pirates (Gunslingers).
The higher it is, the higher the avoidability is. \nIt determines the Thief's attacking ability and hands.\nAlso, the higher it is, the less EXP a character loses by dying.

It can raise the stats of strength, dexterity, stamina, and luck, along with the amount of HP and MP
If raising strength, dexterity, intelligence, or luck, 1 AP will equal an increase of 1 point
If HP or MP, the increase depends on the condition of the character
5 points are given per every level up.

Amount to increase STR, DEX, INT,LUK, HP and MP. For STR, DEX, INT and LUK, every 1 AP used will increase the stats by 1.  For HP and MP, it differs pending on the jobs and characters.  5 Points will be given upon level up.

The stat that impacts the damage caused by physical attacks. This stat is related to strength (STR) for warriors and magicians, dexterity (DEX) for bowmen, strength, dexterity and luck (LUK) for thieves and strength and dexterity for pirates. The above stat and the equipment's physical attack are added to decide on the overall physical attack.
The stat that determines the ability to defend the weapon attack.\nBased on all equipped armors' weapon def.
The stat that determines the success rate and the attacking ability of spells.\nBased on INT and equipped items' magic power.
The stat for defending spells.\nBased on magic def. of every armor that's been equipped.
The stat that determines the accuracy of weapon attack. \nThe higher, the more accurate.\nBased on dexterity and the equipment item options.
The stat that enables the character to avoid weapon damage.\nThe higher it is, the better the character avoids weapon damage.\nBased on dexterity, luck, and the equipment item options.
Can be changed through equipment item options or skills.
Determines the jumping ability.\nCan be changed through equipment item options or skills.
Press Alt on keyboard to jump
Move around, climb up the ladder, and use portals using the arrow keys.
Move to the right to explore new grounds.
